1 minute, then stop the stir. Cook again for another 1 minute stir and continue cooking until done. This stirring will stop it overheating and spilling over in your microwave. It will take roughly 3 minutes to cook in total</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">3. Take out and add a little milk if desired.&nbsp;</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">4. Top with raspberry or strawberry jelly and enjoy!!!</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">Healthy Whole Wheat Muffins&nbsp;</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">INGREDIENTS</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">3 Tbsp Whole wheat flour (you can also use plain flour)</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">&frac12; teaspoon baking powder</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">&frac14; teaspoon ground cinnamon</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">pinch of fine sea salt</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">2 inch piece of banana&nbsp;</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">2 tsp maple syrup/ honey/agave&nbsp;</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">2-1/2 tbsp milk (dairy or non-dairy)</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">1 tablespoon raisins</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">METHOD</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">1. In a microwave safe mug mash up the banana with a fork.</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">2. Add in the rest of the ingredient and mix together until blended. Then stir in the raisins</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">3. Microwave for 45 seconds -1 minute. (timing is based on my 1200W microwave so your timing might vary)</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">4. Enjoy immediately!</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">Omelette</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">INGREDIENTS</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">2 eggs</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">2 tbsp Milk</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">1 scallion/ green onion chopped</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">1 tsp Parsley</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">salt and pepper</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">METHOD</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">1. Add eggs to mug and whisk together with a fork</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">2. Add parsley, scallions, milk, salt and pepper. Whisk until all ingredients are completely mixed together.</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">3. Microwave for one minute. Stir and break up any large chunks of egg.&nbsp;</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">4. Cook for another 45 to 60 seconds or until eggs are set.&nbsp;</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">5. Top with a sprinkle scallions, salt and pepper</span><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" /><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\">6. Enjoy!</span></p>\r\n<h4>&nbsp;</h4>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>','','Video',0,1,'microwave,mug,together,cook,stir,ingredients,potato,your,milk,whisk,sweet,safe,timing,teaspoon,maple,syrup,top,pepper,jelly,salt','2016-06-01 11:59:41','2016-06-01 11:59:41'),(20,'How to make Chili for Beginners','83amCIDbbNk','','Stephanie Manley',4,1,23,0,'Beginner',1,0,0,'','Do you love chili and don\'t know how to cook? Try this simple recipe for how to make a very basic chili. Chili is really easy to make, and you can enjoy a pot of homemade chili tonight.','\r <ul>\r <li>1 medium sized onions, chopped (yellow or white)</li>\r <li>1 pound ground beef</li>\r <li>2 teaspoon salt</li>\r <li>1/8 teaspoon ground black pepper</li>\r <li>2 tablespoons chili powder (you can add additional up to 1 tablespoon)</li>\r <li>1 14.5 ounce cans diced tomatoes</li>\r <li>2 14.5 ounce cans beans (red kidney, pinto, or black beans)</li>\r <li>1 cup tomato juice if desired (V8 is a great substitute)</li>\r </ul>\r <h4>Instructions</h4>\r <p>Brown the ground beef and chopped onions in a medium sized skillet over medium heat. Season ground beef with salt and black pepper as it is browning. Drain beef when browned.</p>\r <p>&nbsp;</p>\r <p>In a medium sized pot add tomatoes, beans, juice, and chili powder. Add cooked ground beef and stir to combine. Simmer for approximately 1 hour before serving.</p>','<h4>Ingredients</h4>\n <ul>\n <li>1 medium sized onions, chopped (yellow or white)</li>\n <li>1 pound ground beef</li>\n <li>2 teaspoon salt</li>\n <li>1/8 teaspoon ground black pepper</li>\n <li>2 tablespoons chili powder (you can add additional up to 1 tablespoon)</li>\n <li>1 14.5 ounce cans diced tomatoes</li>\n <li>2 14.5 ounce cans beans (red kidney, pinto, or black beans)</li>\n <li>1 cup tomato juice if desired (V8 is a great substitute)</li>\n </ul>\n <h4>Instructions</h4>\n <p>Brown the ground beef and chopped onions in a medium sized skillet over medium heat. Season ground beef with salt and black pepper as it is browning. Drain beef when browned.</p>\n<p>In a medium sized pot add tomatoes, beans, juice, and chili powder. Add cooked ground beef and stir to combine. Simmer for approximately 1 hour before serving.</p>','Video',0,1,'chili,ground,beef,sized,black,medium,make,pot,beans,onions,chopped,juice,cans,powder,can,vis,beanscup,tomato,desired,great','2016-06-01 12:18:31','2016-06-01 12:18:31'),(23,'Giant Oreo Cookie Cheesecake','avg9VzBu1mU','','HowToCookThat',2,4,5,0,'Intermediate',1,1,0,'','Step by step recipe tutorial showing how to make a delicious giant Oreo cheesecake in the shape of a giant oreo cookie.','<h4>Cookie Dough for detailing the cake</h4>\r <p><span class=\"italic\">Ingredients:</span></p>\r <p>1 cup or 225g (7.94 ounces) sugar />230g (8.11 ounces) or 1 cup plus 1tbsp and 2 tsp butter<br />1 egg<br />2 1/2 cups or 375g (13.23 ounces) plain flour<br />1/2 cup or 55g (1.94 ounces) cocoa powder<br />70g (2.47 ounces) dark chocolate</p>\r\r <h5>Directions:</h5>\r <p>Beat together the butter and sugar until smooth. Mix in the egg and then the plain flour. Melt the chocolate and work quickly to mix it into the dough. Knead to form a ball and then roll out onto baking paper. &nbsp;Cut out the letters for OREO using letter shaped cookie or playdoh cutters. Cut two triangles, use a straw to cut some mini circles and then cut lots of strips and chop them into rectangles to go around the edge of the cheesecake. Cut out an oval big enough to fit around your letters and then the other shapes as shown in the video. Bake them in the oven at 180 C (356 degrees Fahrenheit) &ndash; they will not take long because they are so thin.</p>\r\r <h4>Fudgey Brownie Base and Top Recipe</h4>\r <p>Ingredients:</p>\r <p>100g (3.53 ounces) or 1/3 cup plus 2 tbsp butter<br />2 eggs<br />1 cup or 218g (7.69 ounces) sugar<br />3/4 cup or 120g (4.23 ounces) self raising flour<br />1/4 cup or 30g (1.06 ounces) cocoa powder<br />200g (7.05 ounces) dark chocolate, roughly chopped</p>\r\r <p>Directions:</p>\r <p>Preheat your oven to 180C (356 degrees Fahrenheit). Grease and line two round 18 cm (7.09 inches) cake tins with baking paper. Place the cookie part of the oreos into a plastic bag and crush with a rolling pin until you have fine crumbs. &nbsp;Put the butter into a bowl and melt it in the microwave. Add the eggs and whisk in. Pour in the sugar and mix well. &nbsp;Add the cocoa powder and self raising flour and whisk through until no lumps remain. &nbsp;Stir through the dark chocolate and the crushed oreos until just combined. Split the mixture evenly between the two tins. &nbsp;Bake in the oven for approximately 15 minutes or until a knife inserted into the centre comes out clean.&nbsp;</p>\r\r <h4>Oreo Cheesecake Filling Recipe</h4>\r <h5>Ingredients:</h5>\r <p>2 tablespoons gelatine dissolved in 1/3 cup water<br />750g (26.46 ounces) cream cheese &ndash; leave out of the fridge to soften while you make the base<br />1 cup or 218g (7.69 ounces) sugar<br />filling from 6 oreos<br />3/4 cup or 190ml milk<br />3/4 cup or 190ml cream<br />Additional 5 oreos chopped roughly</p>\r\r <h5>Directions:</h5>\r <p>Line the base and sides of a 17 cm (6.69 inches) round container with baking paper. The container should be slightly smaller than the size of the base and top. &nbsp;Sprinkle the gelatin over cold water, stir and leave to stand. &nbsp;Beat cream cheese until smooth, add in the sugar and oreo filling. &nbsp;Pour in the milk and cream and mix well. &nbsp;Slowly heat the softened gelatine in the microwave until it is a smooth liquid (if you overheat &nbsp;it will&nbsp;overflow so do 20secs at a time or use a large bowl).</p>\r <p>While the beaters are running pour the gelatin into the mixture.<br />Roughly chop 5 oreos. Pour some mixture into the container and add some chopped oreos to the centre section, add more mixture and continue this until you have used it all. Try to keep the edges completely white by putting the chopped oreo towards the centre. &nbsp;This recipe will serve approximately 15 people.</p>','','Video',0,0,'ounces,org,oreo,out,sugar,cup,cookie,mix,cut,cheesecake,then,flour,dark,some,smooth,giant,paper,oven,two,baking','2016-06-01 12:45:46','2016-06-01 12:45:46'),(30,'Vegan Banoffee Pie','EVTWGrzWM80','','Ela Gale',3,9,5,0,'Beginner',1,0,0,'','Banoffee pie has always been one of my favourite puddings - there is nothing like the combo of caramel, bananas, cream and chocolate! So I was sure I was going to miss it a lot being vegan ... then I made this recipe and I couldn\'t have been more wrong! It\'s so yummy and a lot healthier than conventional banoffee pies while being almost as simple to make.','<h4><br style=\"color: #333333; font-family: Roboto, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px;\" />Caramel Ingredients</h4>\r <ul>\r <li><em>1 cup dates -medjool or dried- soak dried in 1/2 cup water&nbsp;</em></li>\r <li><em>3 tbsp almond butter</em></li>\r <li><em>1 tsp vanilla extract</em></li>\r <li><em>3 tbsp maple syrup&nbsp;</em></li>\r <li><em>pinch salt&nbsp;</em></li>\r </ul>\r <h4>Base Ingredients</h4>\r <ul>\r <li><em>1 cup almond meal</em></li>\r <li><em>1 1/2 cups rolled oats</em></li>\r <li><em>4 tbsp coconut oil</em></li>\r <li><em>4 dates</em></li>\r <li><em>2 tbsp water</em></li>\r </ul>\r <p>180degrees 15min&nbsp;</p>\r <h4>Topping Ingredients</h4>\r <ul>\r <li><em>1 can coconut cream - refrigerated</em></li>\r <li><em>2 tsp icing sugar</em></li>\r <li><em>1 tsp vanilla extract</em></li>\r <li><em>1 banana&nbsp;</em></li>\r <li><em>1 tbsp dark chocolate melted&nbsp;</em></li>\r </ul>\r <p><em>Refrigerate for 2-3 days&nbsp;</em></p>','','Video',0,0,'banoffee,almond,vanilla,coconut,cream,chocolate,vegan,dried,being,been,was,lot,pie,maple,buttertsp,extracttbsp,waternbsptbsp,dates,caramelcup,medjool','2016-06-05 15:48:53','2016-06-05 15:48:53'),(32,'How to peel a potato ( Super Fast )','mbHeddAnrZs','','DaveHax',3,9,13,0,'Beginner',0,0,0,'','This simple trick show you a speedy way to peel your potatoes without using a peeler. Great if you\'ve got a lot of potatoes to peel. You need to boil the potatoes, but you could try parboiling them and then putting them in the oven if you want roast potatoes, or cutting them for chips.','','','Video',0,1,'potatoes,peel,them,could,try,but,boil,need,chips,cutting,parboiling,oven,want,putting,then,lot,roast,youve,simple,trick','2016-06-07 11:38:49','2016-06-07 11:38:49'),(33,'How to Make Perfect Poached Eggs','p633fYhNyqw','','DaveHax',3,9,4,0,'Beginner',0,0,0,'','Here\'s a great cooking tip which shows you how to cook the perfect poached egg with a lovely runny yolk. Really simple Kitchen tip and gives great results.','','','Video',0,1,'tip,poached,great,perfect,really,yolk,runny,simple,results,lovely,kitchen,gives,shows,heres,eggs,cooking,which,cook,make,egg','2016-06-07 11:40:28','2016-06-07 11:40:28'),(34,'How to cook poached eggs the easy way','hRWxY4jx-P4','','Frank Forsey',3,33,4,0,'Beginner',0,0,0,'','A couple of friends in work were interested in my easier poached e